Chapter - 0 (Intro)

Aivora is a browser-based IDE with the following features:
Real-time Collaboration - Supports multiple users editing code simultaneously.
AI Code Suggestions - Provides intelligent suggestions and quick edits using Cmd+K.
AI Assistant - Conversation-based assistant to help with coding tasks.
In-Browser Execution - Runs code directly in the browser using WebContainer.
GitHub Integration - Allows importing and exporting projects from GitHub.
Multi-file Projects - Supports structured projects with multiple files and folders.

Tech Stack 

User Interface
Shadcn/UI - Prebuilt UI components using Tailwind, easy to customize and reuse.
Radix UI - Accessible UI primitives used to build flexible components.

Frontend
Next.js - React framework for building fast and scalable web applications.
React 19 - Library for creating interactive user interfaces with components.
TypeScript - Typed JavaScript that improves code safety and maintainability.
Tailwind CSS 4 - Utility-first CSS framework for designing modern responsive layouts.

Backend
Convex (Real Time DB) - Backend platform with real-time database and server functions.
Inngest (Background Jobs) - Event-driven system for running background jobs and workflows.

Editor
CodeMirror 6 - Flexible browser-based code editor with extension support.
Custom Extensions - Additional editor features built for project-specific functionality.
One Dark Theme - Clean dark theme designed for comfortable coding.

AI
Claude Sonnet - AI model used for intelligent coding assistance.

Auth
Clerk - Authentication service for secure user login and management.

Execution
WebContainer API - Runs a Node.js environment directly inside the browser.
Xterm.js - Browser-based terminal for running command-line operations.


